      "udi": "umb://element/b811e827addd4e3c9c09cc1cf7d369d3",
      "policyDocumentName": "Enhanced Vehicular Emissions Scheme (VES)",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2021",
      "endDate": "2025",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.mot.gov.sg/what-we-do/green-transport/electric-vehicles ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>Rebates for certain categories of vehicles will be increased by $5,000 for cars, and $7,500 for taxis.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "New car owners"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/c5a33615c12940bb8c87ead0bc2664a9",
      "policyDocumentName": "Additional Registration Fee (ARF) floor reduction",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2022",
      "endDate": "2023",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.mot.gov.sg/what-we-do/green-transport/electric-vehicles ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>The ARF floor will be lowered from $5,000 to $0 for fully electric cars and taxis, so that buyers of mass-market electric cars can enjoy the combined EEAI and VES rebates of up to $45,000.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "New car owners"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/43f514c31dda468cb2e4ba9d43056bfd",
      "policyDocumentName": "Revision of road tax framework for electric cars",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2022",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.mot.gov.sg/what-we-do/green-transport/electric-vehicles ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>Road taxes for fully electric and petrol electric cars will be reduced by up to 34 per cent for those whose cars are in the 90-230kW power rating bracket. This is to ensure that mass-market electric cars pay similar road tax quantum compared to their internal combustion engine equivalents.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "EV owners"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/ea331ff4e8054501a420c087be83bb7b",
      "policyDocumentName": "Technical Reference 25",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2010",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/industry_innovations/technologies/electric_vehicles/charging_standard_and_installation_of_ev_chargers.html ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>Provides regulatory standards to develop robust EV eco-system in Singapore. It lays out particulars of EV Charging Systems, licenced experts/ technicians, installation &amp; verification requirements, users responsibilities.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "applicable to EV market/ actors"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/2c041f5cfd35403f8b98eed72a9a918b",
      "policyDocumentName": "EV Common Charger Grant",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2021",
      "endDate": "2025",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/industry_innovations/technologies/electric_vehicles/ev_common_charger_grant.html ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "policyInstruments": "",
      "objectives": "<p>For non-landed private residences such as condominiums and private apartments, EV Common Charger Grant was launched to catalyse the deployment of EV chargers by co-funding installation costs.<br>The ECCG will co-fund installation costs of 2,000 EV chargers at NLPRs, as an early adoption incentive. As NLPRs form a significant proportion of residences in Singapore, improving charger provision and access is an important step towards improving the coverage of Singapore’s national EV charging network. </p>\n<p>Applications for the ECCG opened on 29 July 2021 and will be assessed on a first-come, first-served basis. The ECCG will be available until 31 December 2025, or until 2,000 chargers have been supported by co-funding, whichever is earlier.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "Industry/ commercial"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/f70462ee1c3f4e8f854177e278c0b08b",
      "policyDocumentName": "Nation-Wide EV Car-Sharing Programme: BlueSG",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2017",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.globalfueleconomy.org/media/597460/07_singapore-fuel-economy-initiatives.pdf ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Other",
      "objectives": "<p>A fleet of 1,000 electric cars, with 2,000 supporting electric charging points, to be rolled out progressively within 4 years starting mid-2017. 20% of charging points will be opened up to the public; EV car-sharing to be made available in every single housing estate by 2020.<br>The Land Transport Authority (LTA) has been working closely with BlueSG to identify and secure suitable parking lots across Singapore for the vehicle charging stations.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "Commercial"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/37b6b9593e9b45e585a42cacd19b9465",
      "policyDocumentName": "Launch of an EV Charging Network Module",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2022",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.mot.gov.sg/news/Details/speech-by-minister-for-transport-mr-s-iswaran-at-the-launch-of-the-national-electric-vehicle-campaign-power-every-move-towards-an-ev-ready-future ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "National",
      "objectives": "<p>MOT will enhance EV users’ access to information on the public EV charging network. Currently, EV users may need to log into different applications to find and compare charging points. To give EV users the full picture, LTA has developed a single platform and partnered multiple EV charging operators to aggregate and display key information of charging facilities. This includes the location of the nearest chargers, their prices, and their power rating. This will enable EV users to locate and use charging points more easily. This platform will be available as a new module on the MyTransport.SG Mobile app. With support from industry partners – Bluecharge, CDG ENGIE, Charge+, Shell Recharge, SP Mobility – the app will provide information of over 800 charging points in 200 locations. MOT will continue to improve this module with new features such as real time charging point availability, and welcome other industry partnerships.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "All EV users"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/6b84f0520e1240b8a987ff41f52fb4fe",
      "policyDocumentName": "Adjusted Early Turnover Scheme (ETS) ",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2023",
      "endDate": "2025",
      "sourceLink": "https://onemotoring.lta.gov.sg/content/onemotoring/home/bu ying/vehicle-types-and-registrations/commercial-vehicle/early-turnover.html#:~:text=The%20Early%20Turnover%20Scheme%20(ETS)%20encourages%20you%20to%20replace%20your,PQP)%20for%20your%20replacement%20vehicle.",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>Existing Euro II, III and IV Category C diesel vehicles are eligible for the ETS incentive. The incentives will be based on the type of the existing vehicle and replacement vehicle registered under the ETS. Replacement vehicles without tailpipe emissions will enjoy the highest incentives. The incentive for turnover to Light Commercial Vehicles (LCVs) without tailpipe emissions will be higher than those with tailpipe emissions.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "Old car owners"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/302522416441425fbcdad8b34e5e0c41",
      "policyDocumentName": "Commercial Vehicles Emissions Scheme (CVES)",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "subSector": "Commercial vehicles",
      "startDate": "2021",
      "endDate": "2025",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.nea.gov.sg/media/news/news/index/promoting-the-adoption-of-cleaner-commercial-vehicles ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>Commercial vehicles are categorised into three bands resulting in a $15,000 surcharge for the most pollutive vehicles to $15,000 incentive for the least pollutive vehicles.<br>This encourages buyers to choose commercial vehicle models that have lower emissions across the identified pollutant categories, effective from 1 April 2021 to 31 March 2025.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/52d5a70533164223b142bc80ba83ecab",
      "policyDocumentName": "Enhancements to Fuel Economy Labelling Scheme (FELS)",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "startDate": "2012",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.nccs.gov.sg/media/press-release/carbon-emissions-based-vehicle-scheme-kicks-in-1-january-2013#:~:text=The%20FELS%20label%20is%20required,buyers%20to%20make%20informed%20decisions ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>To assist car buyers make informed decisions, the CO2/km performance data for each car model will be provided on mandatory information labels at car showrooms. LTA will also set up a new FELS online database and online fuel cost calculator so that buyers can easily access and compare the carbon emissions and fuel efficiency performance data across car models. These changes will be made progressively after LTA takes over the administration of the Fuel Economy Labelling Scheme (FELS) from NEA around mid 2012.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "subSector": "New car owners"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/3034907080e843718f479a5beda2b15f",
      "policyDocumentName": "Islandwide Cycling Network (ICN) Programme",
      "sector": "Transport",
      "subSector": "Government agency (new role)",
      "startDate": "2020",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/getting_around/active_mobility/walking_cycling_infrastructure/cycling.html ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>The Land Transport Authority (LTA) will accelerate the building of cycling path networks and active mobility infrastructure across Singapore over the next 10 years under a new Islandwide Cycling Network (ICN) Programme. LTA’s preliminary estimate is that this will cost more than $1 billion. The programme will bring greater convenience and enhanced connectivity to active mobility device users, and improve safety for all path users, including pedestrians.  <br>Cycling Path Networks (CPNs) introduce infrastructural upgrades designed to provide a safe and conducive environment for active mobility users of different ages and proficiency levels to commute around towns with greater ease and convenience.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/419f459f5f1346dbad0deb209c4ac073",
      "policyDocumentName": "\"Energy Conservation Act (ECA) Primarily to mandate energy efficiency for industries, later extended to other sectors (see below)\"",
      "sector": "Industry",
      "startDate": "2013",
      "sourceLink": "https://sso.agc.gov.sg/Act/ECA2012 ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Legislative",
      "objectives": "<h4>Other sources</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nea.gov.sg/our-services/climate-change-energy-efficiency/energy-efficiency/industrial-sector\">https://www.nea.gov.sg/our-services/climate-change-energy-efficiency/energy-efficiency/industrial-sector</a>  </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nccs.gov.sg/media/press-release/singapore-to-improve-energy-efficiency-of-the-industry-sector\">https://www.nccs.gov.sg/media/press-release/singapore-to-improve-energy-efficiency-of-the-industry-sector</a> </p>\n<p>An Act to mandate energy efficiency requirements and energy management practices for  Existing Industrial Facilities to promote energy conservation, improve energy efficiency and reduce environmental impact. The ECA was accompanies by 3 main regulatory tools-<br>1. Energy Conservation (Registrable Corporations) Order 2013<br>2. Energy Conservation (Energy Management Practices) Regulations 2013<br>3. Energy Conservation (Composition of Offences) Regulations 2013</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/4783ce9d8bb94cad8c0c0bae825ec9a7",
      "policyDocumentName": "Mandatory Energy Labelling Scheme (MELS) and Minimum Energy Performance Standards (MEPS) For HOUSEHOLDS",
      "sector": "Household",
      "startDate": "2008",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.nea.gov.sg/our-services/climate-change-energy-efficiency/energy-efficiency/household-sector ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "policyInstruments": "",
      "objectives": "<p>MELS and MEPS help improve the energy efficiency of a range of household appliances. By buying more efficient models with better energy efficiency ratings, households can consume less energy, save money on their electricity bills and help to reduce carbon emissions.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/481dfdfee46948c9b7122c220b092a41",
      "policyDocumentName": "Climate Friendly Households (CFH) Programme",
      "sector": "Household",
      "startDate": "2022",
      "endDate": "2023",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.nea.gov.sg/our-services/climate-change-energy-efficiency/energy-efficiency/household-sector ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>To encourage households to take on climate-friendly action as individuals to reduce energy and water consumption, while saving costs in the long run. The programme aims to provide all 1-, 2-, and 3-room HDB (Gov. subsidized) flats with incentive cash vouchers ($150, $25, and $50) for the purchase of energy efficient  refrigerators, LED lights, and water fittings respectively.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/b27baddb35904ee0abf8754d53183214",
      "policyDocumentName": "\"Energy Efficiency Grant (EEG) \"",
      "sector": "Industry",
      "startDate": "2022",
      "endDate": "2024",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.gobusiness.gov.sg/energy-efficiency-grant/ ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<h4>Second source</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.enterprisesg.gov.sg/financial-support/energy-efficiency-grant\">https://www.enterprisesg.gov.sg/financial-support/energy-efficiency-grant</a></p>\n<p>To help businesses within the Food Services, Food Manufacturing or Retail sectors to cope with rising energy costs, through co-funding investments in more energy efficient equipment (upto 70% funding support, capped at SGD30K). It provides financial support for SMEs to adopt pre-approved energy efficient equipment in the following categories: LED lighting, air-conditioners, cooking hobs, refrigerators, water heaters and clothes dryers.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/4c52d089fdfd4f089ad8aa387a66a3b9",
      "policyDocumentName": "\"Tax incentive for Energy-saving Equipment (under Income Tax Act, for solar energy uptake)\"",
      "sector": "Large industries",
      "startDate": "1996",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.iea.org/policies/4079-tax-incentive-for-energy-saving-equipment ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Legislative",
      "objectives": "<p>This tax incentive scheme is provided under the Income Tax Act. Capital expenditure on qualifying energy efficient or energy-saving equipment can be written off in 1 year instead of 3. Qualifying equipment include: solar heating or cooling system and solar energy collection systems. Capital expenditure pertains to costs incurred by the investment in or purchase of long-term business assets. </p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/7f4fc247cc5249058e58830f8af52b24",
      "policyDocumentName": "SolarNova Program",
      "sector": "Government agencies, housing sector",
      "startDate": "2014",
      "endDate": "2022",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.hdb.gov.sg/about-us/our-role/smart-and-sustainable-living/solarnova-page  ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<h4>Other sources</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.hdb.gov.sg/about-us/news-and-publications/press-releases/HDB-to-bring-solar-energy\">https://www.hdb.gov.sg/about-us/news-and-publications/press-releases/HDB-to-bring-solar-energy</a><br><a href=\"https://getsolar.ai/blog/solar-financial-incentives-singapore-2/\">https://getsolar.ai/blog/solar-financial-incentives-singapore-2/</a><br><a href=\"https://www.ema.gov.sg/consumer-information/solar/solar-installation-guide\">https://www.ema.gov.sg/consumer-information/solar/solar-installation-guide</a></p>\n<p>It is a Whole-Of-Government effort led by the Economic Development Board (EDB) and HDB to accelerate the deployment of solar photovoltaic (PV) systems in Singapore. This programme helps to promote and aggregate demand for solar PV across government agencies to achieve economies of scale, as well as drive the growth of Singapore’s solar industry. AID SOLAR DEPLOYMENT IN Housing blocks, floating farms, industrial areas.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/0b33ec8bcefd430e99a9254cdc1cf190",
      "policyDocumentName": "SolarRoof Program",
      "sector": "Industry",
      "startDate": "2020",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.jtc.gov.sg/get-help/managing-your-tenancy-or-lease/solar-deployment",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<h4>Other sources</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.jtc.gov.sg/enhance-your-business/be-more-sustainable#solarise-your-development\">https://www.jtc.gov.sg/enhance-your-business/be-more-sustainable#solarise-your-development</a><br><a href=\"https://getsolar.ai/blog/solar-financial-incentives-singapore-2/\">https://getsolar.ai/blog/solar-financial-incentives-singapore-2/</a><br><br></p>\n<p>The solar deployment across all JTC buildings as well as on sea will increase the solar capacity from the current 135.6MWp to about 350MWp, when fully completed by 2030. Privately leased industrial properties account for 72% of total potential solar capacity from industrial estates and outreach efforts will be ramped up for a collaborative push with industrialists to increase the current capacity of 225.4 MWp to 900 MWp by 2030. Collectively, roll-out across all feasible JTC buildings and vacant industrial land, privately leased industrial properties, as well as the deployment of floating solar photovoltaic panel systems close to Jurong Island can potentially generate 1,250 MWp, contributing to 60 per cent of Singapore's total solar deployment target of at least 2 GWp by 2030.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/e0621deebed54d419b36e45d553c2e26",
      "policyDocumentName": "SolarLand Program",
      "sector": "Industry",
      "startDate": "2020",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.jtc.gov.sg/about-jtc/news-and-stories/press-releases/jtc-leads-solar-deployment-across-singapore-industrial-estates ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>The SolarLand programme by JTC involves installing modular solar PV systems on temporary vacant land. These solar PV systems are currently found on Jurong Island and at Changi Business Park.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/95d23309a6a7427daf61d15fb4121bdc",
      "policyDocumentName": "Singapore Standard (SS) 673: Code of Practice for Renewable Energy Certificates (RECs).",
      "sector": "Commercial & residential",
      "startDate": "2021",
      "sourceLink": "https://www.ema.gov.sg/news-events/news/media-releases/new-singapore-standard-launch-to-support-management-and-use-of-renewable-energy-certificates ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<p>Intended to provide a clear framework to improve the integrity of measurement, reporting and verification (MRV) requirements for the issuance and management of RECs. It covers guidelines across the lifecycle of RECs – from production, tracking, management, to the usage of the certificates for renewable energy claims in Singapore.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/cccb3f443c8648bcb80e3c3a328c0999",
      "sector": "international collaboration",
      "subSector": "",
      "startDate": "2022",
      "sourceLink": "https://policy.asiapacificenergy.org/node/2574 ",
      "policyLevel": "Other",
      "policyOrigin": "Other",
      "policyInstruments": "",
      "objectives": "<p>This Pilot project entitled was created in order to study cross border power trade from Lao PDR to Singapore. It will serve as a pathfinder to complement existing efforts towards realizing the ASEAN Power Grid (APG) and the ASEAN Economic Community (AEC), by creating opportunities for electricity trading beyond neighboring borders. This initiative will contribute towards energy security by strengthening the power integration network and enhancing the economic prosperity of the region. The project is also expected to help identify and resolve issues affecting cross – border electricity trading in ASEAN.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ],
      "policyDocumentName": "Lao PDR-Thailand-Malaysia-Singapore Power Integration Project  (Not a policy per se but has policy components)"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/0b4c12868fec4d1297a5873767dd9544",
      "policyDocumentName": "\"MOU on Renewable Energy Cooperation. (with Indonesia)\"",
      "sector": "international collaboration",
      "subSector": "",
      "startDate": "2023",
      "objectives": "<p>A planned collaboration</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/f6ccf1d475284275ae2691fc24e46818",
      "policyDocumentName": "The Building Control (Environmental Sustainability) Regulations",
      "sector": "All buildings",
      "startDate": "2008",
      "sourceLink": "https://www1.bca.gov.sg/buildsg/sustainability/regulatory-requirements-for-new-buildings-existing-buildings-undergoing-major-aanda ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Legislative",
      "objectives": "<p>To advance sustainable development, the Building Control (Environmental Sustainability) Regulations requires a minimum environmental sustainability standard for new buildings and existing buildings that undergo major retrofitting.  </p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
      "udi": "umb://element/bd1c48512d774d0aa7db412af2e1ab14",
      "policyDocumentName": "BCA Green Mark Certification Scheme",
      "sector": "Commercial sector",
      "startDate": "2005",
      "sourceLink": "https://www1.bca.gov.sg/buildsg/sustainability/green-mark-certification-scheme  ",
      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Bureaucratic",
      "objectives": "<h4>Second source</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www1.bca.gov.sg/buildsg/sustainability/green-mark-certification-scheme/green-mark-2021\">https://www1.bca.gov.sg/buildsg/sustainability/green-mark-certification-scheme/green-mark-2021</a></p>\n<p>The BCA Green Mark 2021 (GM: 2021) is an internationally recognised green building certification scheme tailored for the tropical climate. It encourages the industry and professionals to collaborate and develop green building solutions, raising Singapore’s built environment’s sustainability standards. BCA Green Mark 2021 (GM: 2021) aims to raise our standards in energy performance and place greater emphasis on other sustainability outcomes.</p>",
      "policyInventoryCountry": [
        "Singapore"
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f10d08d3-d4e4-4111-adeb-82ecc0e7d452",
