      "policyLevel": "National",
      "policyOrigin": "Other",
      "objectives": "<p>In 2023, the Thai government allocated THB 24 billion to subsidise the production of battery cells for Electric Vehicles (EVs). This subsidiary mechanism is implemented through “the EV Board” as a commitment to meet Thailand's national target of 30% of the total electric car production by 2030. </p>\n<p>The subsidies intend to reduce the cost of production, aiming at cheaper prices for EVs in domestic markets. </p>",
