      "objectives": "<h4>Other sources</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.iea.org/policies/6638-eco-car-programme-excise-tax?country=Thailand\">https://www.iea.org/policies/6638-eco-car-programme-excise-tax?country=Thailand</a><br><a href=\"https://www.fuelsandlubes.com/knowledge-base/thailand-to-tax-vehicles-based-on-co2-emissions-by-2016/\">https://www.fuelsandlubes.com/knowledge-base/thailand-to-tax-vehicles-based-on-co2-emissions-by-2016/</a></p>\n<p>From 2012, there is an eight-year exemptions from corporate income tax (with a cap) for investment in advanced vehicle parts tech (includes HEVs, PHEVs, BEVs batteries, and traction motors for hybrid/fuel-cell cars. The years of exemption can be extended based on the share of R&amp;D expenditures in their total revenues.</p>",
