      "objectives": "<p>Between January and April 2023, the Thai government allocated THB 75 billion for electricity subsidies to mitigate the effects of energy price increases. Reductions in electricity bills will be granted to households using up to 300 units of electricity per month and residing within the regions covered by the services specified in the Royal Thai concessions contract.</p>",
